## Summary

The static function `header_name_valid_for_serialize` (lines 81-90) is only called once in the entire file, making it a candidate for inlining to improve code locality.

## Location

**File**: `src/http/SocketHTTP1-serialize.c`
**Lines**: 81-90 (10 lines)
**Called at**: Line 121 in `serialize_header_cb`

## Current Code

```c
static int
header_name_valid_for_serialize (const char *name, size_t len)
{
  for (size_t i = 0; i < len; i++)
    {
      unsigned char c = (unsigned char)name[i];
      if (c == '\r' || c == '\n' || c == '\0' || c == ':')
        return 0;
    }
  return len > 0;
}
```

**Single call site** (line 121):
```c
if (!header_name_valid_for_serialize (name, name_len)
    || !header_value_valid_for_serialize (value, value_len))
  {
    return -1; /* Reject headers with control characters */
  }
```

## Recommendation

Inline this 10-line validation function directly into its only call site at line 121 to:
- Improve code locality and readability
- Reduce function call overhead (minor performance benefit)
- Eliminate unnecessary abstraction for single-use logic

## Pattern

- **Type**: SINGLE_USE_INLINE
- **Severity**: HIGH (small function, clear inline candidate)
- **Category**: Refactoring / Readability

## Related

This is part of a broader pattern in this file - see also `header_value_valid_for_serialize` which has the same issue.
